# ElizaOS Levva Agent - Project Overview

This is an ElizaOS agent implementation designed to improve UX for the Levva staking protocol (https://levva.fi/). 

## Core Functionality
- Swapping different crypto assets via Kyber and Pendle integrations
- Analyzing user portfolios and wallet assets
- Suggesting investment strategies (ultra-safe, safe, brave, custom)
- Managing DeFi positions with leverage through pools and vaults
- Providing crypto news and market insights

## Architecture
- **ElizaOS Framework**: TypeScript-based AI agent framework
- **Plugin System**: Modular architecture with actions, providers, services, evaluators
- **Database**: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM
- **Blockchain**: Multi-chain support (Ethereum, Arbitrum, Base) via Viem
- **AI Models**: OpenAI/OpenRouter integration for LLM capabilities
- **Package Manager**: Use Bun instead of npm for all package management and script execution

## Key Components
- **Actions**: Core agent behaviors (swap, strategy selection, wallet analysis)
- **Providers**: Data suppliers (user info, tokens, strategy params, swap params)
- **Services**: Business logic (LevvaService, BrowserService)
- **Evaluators**: Post-action processors (suggestions, transaction acknowledgment)
- **Routes**: HTTP API endpoints for external integrations